TY  - JOUR
AU  - Ely, Jeffrey C.
AU  - Pęski, Marcin
T1  - Critical Types
PY  - 2011
Y1  - 2011/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/restud/rdq035
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 78
IS  - 3
SP  - 907
EP  - 937
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - How can we know in advance whether simplifying assumptions about beliefs will make a difference in the conclusions of game-theoretic models? We define critical types to be types whose rationalizable correspondence is sensitive to assumptions about arbitrarily high-order beliefs. We show that a type is critical if and only if it exhibits common belief in some non-trivial event. We use this characterization to show that all types in commonly used type spaces are critical. On the other hand, we show that regular types (types that are not critical) are generic, although perhaps inconvenient to use in applications.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/restud/rdq035
ER  - 



